/**
 * Builds consumption load curves (profiling) at PRM and RFP levels.
 *
 * <h3>Template cache</h3>
 * Sub-profile curves (AJUSTE + DYNAMIQUE) are shared across all PRMs in a batch run.
 * After the first load per sub-profile, the merged {@code double[]} is stored in
 * {@link #templateCache} (indexed by {@link TemplateKey}).  Every call to
 * {@link #handleMeterReading} obtains a <em>read-only</em> reference to that array,
 * then works on a slice copy produced by {@link CdcOptimized#getReducedCdc}.
 * This eliminates repeated {@code convertBytesToDoubles} calls that showed up heavily
 * in Glowroot profiling (≈ one call per PRM per sub-profile → O(PRMs × sub-profiles)).
 */
public class CurveProfilingScript extends Script {
